cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

This paper deals with Natural Language Processing and Deep Learning models, which are typically covered in the Computer Science sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the interpretability of deep architectures, which is a topic of interest in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a method to reduce the structure of the autoencoder without loss of classification accuracy, which falls under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the produced structures using human judgment, which is a common practice in the sub-category of Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
